              /
              
slope m = your speed
at that exact moment!
```

---

## Connecting Everything

```
WALKING          MATH
──────────────────────────
Distance    →   y
Time        →   x
Speed       →   slope (m)
Where home  →   b (intercept)
Slowing down→   curve
Exact speed →   derivative
Zooming in  →   calculus!
```

---

## Super Simple Summary 🎯

```
Straight line = constant speed
     y = mx + b

Curve = changing speed
     calculus zooms in
     finds y = mx + b
     at every point
     
That slope = exact speed
at that moment!
```

> **Calculus is just finding your exact speed at any moment of your journey!** 🚶


